UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1949
1 across every state and territory, with more than 300,000 staff and 350,000 volunteers
2 delivering essential programs to over 17 million people annually, including almost 11
3 million adults, and 6.5 million children and youth; and
4 WHEREAS, 17 YMCAs, 3000 staff members, and hundreds of volunteers in
5 Kentucky provide critical services including childcare, afterschool enrichment, summer
6 camps, teen leadership programs, swim safety lessons, senior wellness programs, and
7 access to nutritious meals to more than 150,000 individuals annually; and
8 WHEREAS, the YMCA is a leader in providing swim lessons, camping programs,
9 youth sports, meal programs, lifestyle health, and fitness and well-being programs, and is
10 the largest provider of fitness programs for older adults; and
11 WHEREAS, the YMCA serves people of all ages, backgrounds, and abilities,
12 creating spaces where all people feel welcome, are treated with respect, and find
13 opportunities to connect with their neighbors; and
14 WHEREAS, YMCAs across the nation are working to build stronger, more
15 connected communities through intentional experiences that help people achieve their
16 goals, foster connection, and promote well-being in order to build relationships and
17 thrive;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
20 Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby honor and express appreciation to
22 the YMCA for 175 years of service to the nation, and recognize the YMCA’s role in
23 responding to community needs, fostering belonging, creating connection, and supporting
24 families and individuals across generations.
25 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
26 Resolution to Senator Amanda Mays Bledsoe.
